'''Owari Shrine''' (おばりじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|lt=Komaki City|Q389537|WD=Q389537|1=Komaki}}, {{ill|lt=Aichi Prefecture|Q80434|WD=Q80434|1=Aichi Prefecture}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Amenokayama no Mikoto|Q10940849|WD=Q10940849|1=Ame-no-Kaguyama}}
* {{ill|lt=Emperor Ōjin|Q317997|WD=Q317997|WD=Q317997|lt=Hondawake no Mikoto|1=Emperor Ōjin}}
* {{ill|lt=Ōkuninushi|Q276944|WD=Q276944|lt=Ōnamuchi no Mikoto|1=Ōkuninushi}}

=== History ===
The date of foundation is unknown. Until the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Edo period|1=Edo period|WD=Q184963}}, it was called '''Sannō'''.

Because the location was formerly Kobari Village in {{ill|lt=Kasugai District|Q11513576|WD=Q11513576|1=Kasugai district}}, and the village name resembled “{{ill|lt=Owari Province|Q514506|WD=Q514506|1=Owari Province}},” from the Edo period onward it came to be identified with the Shikinaisha “Owari Shrine” of {{ill|lt=Yamada District (Owari Province)|Q11470699|WD=Q11470699|lt=Yamada District|1=Yamada district, Owari}}, and was said to be the place of origin of the name “Owari Province.” In {{ill|lt=Shōwa|Q327567|WD=Q327567|1=Shōwa era}} 15 ({{ill|lt=1940|Q18633|WD=Q18633|1=1940}}), the local {{ill|lt=youth association|Q9334930|WD=Q9334930|1=Seinendan}} erected a {{ill|lt=stone monument|Q178743|WD=Q178743|1=Stele}} engraved with “Place of Origin of the Name Owari” beside the {{ill|lt=torii|Q234731|WD=Q234731|1=Torii}}.

However, later research revealed that this area had belonged not to Yamada District but to {{ill|lt=Kasugai District|Q11513576|WD=Q11513576|lt=Harube District|1=Kasugai district}} since {{ill|lt=ancient times|Q41493|WD=Q41493|1=Ancient history}}, and skepticism has grown regarding the theory that identifies this shrine with the Shikinaisha “Owari Shrine,” which should have been located in Yamada District {{Sfn|Moriyama City Board of Education|1963|p=111}}. The territory of Yamada District is thought to have been south of the {{ill|lt=Shōnai River|Q7506182|WD=Q7506182|1=Shōnai River}}, and theories regarding the original “Owari Shrine” include identifying it with Hakusan Shrine in {{ill|lt=Obata-naka|Q42172480|WD=Q42172480|1=Obata-naka}}, {{ill|lt=Moriyama Ward|Q1155291|WD=Q1155291|1=Moriyama-ku, Nagoya}}, {{ill|lt=Nagoya City|Q11751|WD=Q11751|1=Nagoya}}, or with {{ill|lt=Owarito Shrine|Q11465305|WD=Q11465305|1=Owari-to Shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Kamishidami|Q52306359|WD=Q52306359|1=Kamishidami, Nagoya}}, the same ward {{Sfn|Moriyama City Board of Education|1963|p=111}}.

